<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="161" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="8.[136,1452,158,617]" pageId="8" pageNumber="161">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,265,338,364]" pageId="8" pageNumber="161">Notes:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName box="[294,571,338,364]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="8" pageNumber="161" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="angustipetala">
<emphasis box="[294,571,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="161">Bertolonia angustipetala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to 
<collectingRegion box="[732,800,338,364]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="8" pageNumber="161">Bahia</collectingRegion>
, occurring in montane rainforests (
<figureCitation box="[1186,1269,338,365]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[136,229,1949,1971]" captionTargetBox="[341,1239,654,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-255@5.[340,1247,641,1924]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Distributions of species of Bertolonia in Bahia.A. Bertolonia alternifolia. B. Bertolonia angustipetala. C. Bertolonia bullata. D. Bertolonia carmoi. E. Bertolonia cuspidata. F. Bertolonia hirsutissima. G. Bertolonia igrapiuna. H. Bertolonia kollmannii." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6597686" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6597686/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="161">Fig. 3b</figureCitation>
). Collected with flowers in December and fruits in May and December. 
<taxonomicName box="[761,1041,374,400]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="8" pageNumber="161" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="angustipetala">
<emphasis box="[761,1041,374,400]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="161">Bertolonia angustipetala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by the small (3.9–8 × 
<quantity box="[160,288,410,437]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.75" metricValueMax="3.7" metricValueMin="1.8" pageId="8" pageNumber="161" unit="cm" value="2.75" valueMax="3.7" valueMin="1.8">1.8–3.7 cm</quantity>
) and elliptic leaf blades, these sparsely glandulose-punctate, and linear-lanceolate and apiculate petals. It shares with 
<taxonomicName authority="Bacci &amp; Amorim" authorityName="Bacci &amp; Amorim" box="[303,750,446,472]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="8" pageNumber="161" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cuspidata">
<emphasis box="[303,541,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="161">Bertolonia cuspidata</emphasis>
Bacci &amp; Amorim
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="Bacci, L. F. &amp; Amorim, A. M. &amp; Michelangeli, F. A. &amp; Goldenberg, R." box="[791,1068,446,473]" pageId="8" pageNumber="161" pagination="767 - 792" refId="ref18533" refString="Bacci, L. F., Amorim, A. M., Michelangeli, F. A. &amp; Goldenberg, R. (2018) Increased Sampling in Under-Collected Areas Sheds New Light on the Diversity and Distribution of Bertolonia, an Atlantic Forest Endemic Genus. Systematic Botany 43 (3): 767 - 792. https: // doi. org / 10.1600 / 036364418 X 697490" type="journal article" year="2018">
Bacci 
<emphasis box="[865,917,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="161">et al</emphasis>
. (2018: 772)
</bibRefCitation>
the membranaceous, glandulosepunctate leaf blades with entire margins. However, 
